# SPECBOOT Workflow State Machine

Infer the current stage from artifacts in `openspec/changes/<change-name>/`:

| Stage | Artifacts present | Next command |
|-------|-------------------|--------------|
| Start | none | `/enrich-us` |
| Enriched | `user-story.md` only | `/propose` |
| Proposed | + `proposal.md`, `design.md`, `tasks.md`, delta spec | `/apply` |
| Applying | branch + partial tasks | `/apply` (loop) or `/verify` when tasks done |
| Verifying | all tasks checked + `testing-report.md` | `/verify` |
| Reviewing | verify checklist complete, summary not ready | `/code-review` |
| Archiving | review complete, summary `ready` | `/archive` |
| Committing | `proposal.md` status = `archived` | `/commit` |

## Gate Enforcement

- Do not run `/propose` without `user-story.md`.
- Do not run `/apply` without proposal artifacts and delta spec.
- Do not run `/verify` before implementation tasks are complete.
- Do not run `/code-review` before verify checklist is filled.
- Do not run `/archive` while critical review blockers exist.
- Do not run `/commit` without explicit user approval.

When the user invokes a command out of order, state the current stage and the required prerequisite command.

Resolve `<domain>` from `openspec/config.yaml` (`domain` field) when checking delta spec paths.
